column2: with Martin Billings--sample taken through hole in ice-covered lake
Larry M + Gil K present--lake looks green + turbid--attempts ot rake up aquatic plants revealed only dying stalks

volunteers Larry Mulholland + Gil Kenning present--overcast--air temp 77.2 F--random rakes showed no live aquatic plant except at near-shore area--lake is higher since being refilled- but water is much more turbid
air temp 71.4 F--Larry M + Gil K present air temp 71.4 F--Larry M + Gil K along--lake looking turbid--again tried raking up plants from middle of lake- but got only dead stalks
Water is very Brown and Green No Visible weeds  Air temp 71 and sunny
wind picking up--air temp 62.4 F--lake water continues to be very turbid
Clear and sunny day a few floating plants water murky  temp was 85
chilly and wet with slight wind--no one out on lake--very overcast
